#+TITLE: VM
#+AUTHOR: ciglesia

** Computer System

  +------+-----+------------+-----+-----------------+
  |           CPU           |     |       RAM       |
  +------+------------+-----|     |-----------------+
  | REGS |    ALU     |     |     |   Instructions  |
  +------+------------+-----|     |------+----------+
  |  R0  | Arithmetic | IR  |     | Addr | Mem Cell |
  |  R1  | Logic Unit | PC  |     +------+----------+
  |  R2  |            | PSR |     |  0   |    0     |
  |  ... |            |     |     |  1   |    22    |
  +------+------------+-----+-----+------+----------+

Components:
1. R*
   - General Purpose Registers (/memory cell/)
   - *Register* is _synonym_ for *memory* in /computer science/


*** PROCESS REGISTER
1. *REG_SIZE* (bytes)
2. *REG_NUMBER*

| REGISTER | SIZE     |
|----------+----------|
| r0       | REG_SIZE |
| r1       | REG_SIZE |
| ...      | ...      |
| PC       | REG_SIZE |

*** PROCESS
Available:
1. *REG_NUMBER* registries
2. *PC* (Program Counter)
   - Registry
   - Address->next set of instructions
3. *carry* (Boolean)
   - Last operatiton /success/

** IMPLEMENTATION
Every registry is at 0 except:
1. *r1*
   - Only the first process at startup
   - r1 = number of player
   - Generated by the machine or specified at lunch
2. *PC*
